item.turbo:content:
<! [CDATA[
Internet Explorer Logo
Internet Explorer is a series of discontinued graphical web browsers developed by Microsoft and included in the Microsoft Windows line of operating systems, starting in 1995. It was first released as part of the add-on package Plus! for Windows 95 that year. Later versions were available as free downloads, or in-service packs, and included in the original equipment manufacturer service releases of Windows 95 and later versions of Windows. New feature development for the browser was discontinued in 2016 in favor of new browser Microsoft Edge.
You can download theInternet Explorerlogo on full-version of the page.
]] >

item.turbo:content:
<! [CDATA[
Microsoft Edge Logo
Microsoft Edge is a cross-platform web browser created and developed by Microsoft. It was first released for Windows 10 and Xbox One in 2015, for Android and iOS in 2017, for macOS in 2019, and as a preview for Linux in October 2020, and can replace Internet Explorer 11 on Windows 8.1, Windows Server 2012 R2, Windows Server 2016 and Windows Server 2019 but unlike IE11, this version does not support Windows Vista or an earlier version.
You can download theMicrosoft Edgelogo on full-version of the page.
]] >

item.turbo:content:
<! [CDATA[
Safari Logo
Safari is a graphical web browser developed by Apple, mostly based on open-source software such as WebKit. It first appeared as part of Mac OS X Panther on the Mac in 2003; later, a mobile version was introduced as part of iPhone OS 1 on the iPhone and iPod touch in 2007. It is currently supported on macOS, iOS, and iPadOS. A Windows version was available from 2007 to 2012.
You can download theSafarilogo on full-version of the page.
